Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a drab-coloured pottery jar, the fabric is relatively coarse and grey-pink in section, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and remains of one line of black-painted hieratic text 'year 12'.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393493) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393493)
